subSubSection.paragraph:
The present species fits the recently described genus 

Eulimacrostoma

, because it has a subcylindrical protoconch (
Figure 9H
), microsculpture of very thin axial lines on the teleoconch (
Figure 9E
), an aperture gaping anteriorly (
Figure 9F
) and a strongly protruding outer lip (
Figure 9G
) (
Souza & Pimenta 2019a
).
